Diffusion processes on complex networks - assignment 6

Mateusz Dzitkowski 249777

Exercise 1

We are presented with a q-voter model with independence. We are tasked with implementing the model with the $NN$ influence group and plotting the magnetization as a function of time for various parameters, and the final magnetization as a function of $p$, averaged over $100$ runs.

Here are the results:

In[5]:
import networkx as nx

from main import (
    plot_average_final_magnetization,
    plot_time_evolution_of_magnetization,
    nn_q_panel,
)

N = 100

First, the time evolution of magnetization for $p \in [0, 0.5]$, and the $NN4$ q-panel and for given graph topologies:

  • complete graph ($N = 100$)
  • $BA(100, 4)$
  • $WS(100, 4, 0.01)$
  • $WS(100, 4, 0.2)$
In[2]:
plot_time_evolution_of_magnetization(
    graph=nx.complete_graph(N),
    q_panel=nn_q_panel(4),    
)
In[3]:
plot_time_evolution_of_magnetization(
    graph=nx.barabasi_albert_graph(N, 4),
    q_panel=nn_q_panel(4),    
)
In[4]:
plot_time_evolution_of_magnetization(
    graph=nx.watts_strogatz_graph(N, 4, 0.01),
    q_panel=nn_q_panel(4),    
)
In[5]:
plot_time_evolution_of_magnetization(
    graph=nx.watts_strogatz_graph(N, 4, 0.2),
    q_panel=nn_q_panel(4),    
)

Now do the same with $NN3$ q-panel:

And finally, final magnetization as a function of $p$, for different topologies and $q=3$, and $q=4$, and also for different $q$, with the $WS(100, 4, 0.01)$ topology.

In[2]:
plot_average_final_magnetization(
    graphs={
        "C": nx.complete_graph(N),
        "BA4": nx.barabasi_albert_graph(N, 4),
        "WS01": nx.watts_strogatz_graph(N, 4, 0.01),
        "WS2": nx.watts_strogatz_graph(N, 4, 0.2),
    },
    q_panels={
        "NN3": nn_q_panel(3),
    },
)
In[3]:
plot_average_final_magnetization(
